\title{Oauth Integrations}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Implement OAuth 2.0 authentication with GitHub and Microsoft Entra (Azure AD) in Cloudflare Workers and other edge environments. Covers provider-specific quirks, required headers, scope requirements, and token handling without MSAL.
 Use when: implementing GitHub OAuth, Microsoft/Azure AD authentication, handling OAuth callbacks, or troubleshooting 403 errors in OAuth flows.}

\subtree{
\title{OAuth Integrations for Edge Environments}
\p{Implement GitHub and Microsoft OAuth in Cloudflare Workers and other edge runtimes.}

\subtree{
\title{GitHub OAuth}
\subtree{
\title{Required Headers}
\p{GitHub API has strict requirements that differ from other providers.}

\pre{\startverb
| Header | Requirement |
|--------|-------------|
| `User-Agent` | **REQUIRED** - Returns 403 without it |
| `Accept` | `application/vnd.github+json` recommended |
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
const resp = await fetch('https://api.github.com/user', {
  headers: {
    Authorization: `Bearer ${accessToken}`,
    'User-Agent': 'MyApp/1.0',  // Required!
    'Accept': 'application/vnd.github+json',
  },
});
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Private Email Handling}
\p{GitHub users can set email to private (\code{\startverb /user\stopverb} returns \code{\startverb email: null\stopverb}).}

\pre{\startverb
if (!userData.email) {
  const emails = await fetch('https://api.github.com/user/emails', { headers })
    .then(r => r.json());
  userData.email = emails.find(e => e.primary && e.verified)?.email;
}
\stopverb}

\p{Requires \code{\startverb user:email\stopverb} scope.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Token Exchange}
\p{Token exchange returns form-encoded by default. Add Accept header for JSON:}

\pre{\startverb
const tokenResponse = await fetch('https://github.com/login/oauth/access_token', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded',
    'Accept': 'application/json',  // Get JSON response
  },
  body: new URLSearchParams({ code, client_id, client_secret, redirect_uri }),
});
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{GitHub OAuth Notes}
\pre{\startverb
| Issue | Solution |
|-------|----------|
| Callback URL | Must be EXACT - no wildcards, no subdirectory matching |
| Token exchange returns form-encoded | Add `'Accept': 'application/json'` header |
| Tokens don't expire | No refresh flow needed, but revoked = full re-auth |
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Microsoft Entra (Azure AD) OAuth}
\subtree{
\title{Why MSAL Doesn't Work in Workers}
\p{MSAL.js depends on:}

\ul{
\li{Browser APIs (localStorage, sessionStorage, DOM)}
\li{Node.js crypto module}
}

\p{Cloudflare's V8 isolate runtime has neither. Use manual OAuth instead:}

\ol{
\li{Manual OAuth URL construction}
\li{Direct token exchange via fetch}
\li{JWT validation with \code{\startverb jose\stopverb} library}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Required Scopes}
\pre{\startverb
// For user identity (email, name, profile picture)
const scope = 'openid email profile User.Read';

// For refresh tokens (long-lived sessions)
const scope = 'openid email profile User.Read offline_access';
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Critical}: \code{\startverb User.Read\stopverb} is required for Microsoft Graph \code{\startverb /me\stopverb} endpoint. Without it, token exchange succeeds but user info fetch returns 403.}
}

\subtree{
\title{User Info Endpoint}
\pre{\startverb
// Microsoft Graph /me endpoint
const resp = await fetch('https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/me', {
  headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${accessToken}` },
});

// Email may be in different fields
const email = data.mail || data.userPrincipalName;
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Tenant Configuration}
\pre{\startverb
| Tenant Value | Who Can Sign In |
|--------------|-----------------|
| `common` | Any Microsoft account (personal + work) |
| `organizations` | Work/school accounts only |
| `consumers` | Personal Microsoft accounts only |
| `{tenant-id}` | Specific organization only |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Azure Portal Setup}
\ol{
\li{App Registration → New registration}
\li{Platform: \strong{Web} (not SPA) for server-side OAuth}
\li{Redirect URIs: Add both \code{\startverb /callback\stopverb} and \code{\startverb /admin/callback\stopverb}}
\li{Certificates & secrets → New client secret}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Token Lifetimes}
\pre{\startverb
| Token Type | Default Lifetime | Notes |
|------------|------------------|-------|
| Access token | 60-90 minutes | Configurable via token lifetime policies |
| Refresh token | 90 days | Revoked on password change |
| ID token | 60 minutes | Same as access token |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Best Practice}: Always request \code{\startverb offline_access\stopverb} scope and implement refresh token flow for sessions longer than 1 hour.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Corrections}
\pre{\startverb
| If Claude suggests... | Use instead... |
|----------------------|----------------|
| GitHub fetch without User-Agent | Add `'User-Agent': 'AppName/1.0'` (REQUIRED) |
| Using MSAL.js in Workers | Manual OAuth + jose for JWT validation |
| Microsoft scope without User.Read | Add `User.Read` scope |
| Fetching email from token claims only | Use Graph `/me` endpoint |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Error Reference}
\subtree{
\title{GitHub Errors}
\pre{\startverb
| Error | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| 403 Forbidden | Missing User-Agent header | Add User-Agent header |
| `email: null` | User has private email | Fetch `/user/emails` with `user:email` scope |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Microsoft Errors}
\pre{\startverb
| Error | Cause | Fix |
|-------|-------|-----|
| AADSTS50058 | Silent auth failed | Use interactive flow |
| AADSTS700084 | Refresh token expired | Re-authenticate user |
| 403 on Graph /me | Missing User.Read scope | Add User.Read to scopes |
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Reference}
\ul{
\li{GitHub API: https://docs.github.com/en/rest}
\li{GitHub OAuth: https://docs.github.com/en/apps/oauth-apps}
\li{Microsoft Graph permissions: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/permissions-reference}
\li{AADSTS error codes: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/entra/identity-platform/reference-error-codes}
}
}
}